cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper describes a data-driven solution to a class of sequential decision-making problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of reinforcement learning (RL) and advantage actor critic (A2C) algorithms further supports the likelihood of the paper belonging to the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The applications of the proposed solution to computing systems and operations research suggest the relevance of the paper to the cs.RO and cs.SY sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a large number of concurrent decisions and the use of a vector representation of the decision-making problem suggest a potential connection to the cs.DS sub-category.
